{"id":14880947,"mediaExerciseId":"7ded33c8-6e68-4699-8258-264045784ed2","exerciseName":"9","chapterName":"6","chapterTitle":"Discounted Cash Flow Valuation","groupId":612301,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":184,"solutions":[{"id":5967411,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will determine the annual loan payment if Prescott Bank presents a $75,000 five-year loan with an interest of 6.8%.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"To calculate the loan payment required, we will utilize the PMT function on a spreadsheet. The PMT function is a financial function that can calculate the repayment value based on the interest rate, number of periods, and the present value of the loan.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/01fa8584ee65715bd9fb2e8063ac24fe/e696bc150c098c57fbf11ba4d4a73f68/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/09/01fa8584ee65715bd9fb2e8063ac24fe/e696bc150c098c57fbf11ba4d4a73f68/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The spreadsheet PMT function formula is as follows:\n\n$$\\begin{aligned}\nPMT&=(rate, nper,pv,[fv],[type]) \\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nWhere:\n\n$rate$, which refers to the interest rate\n\n$nper$, represent the period\n\n$pv$, which means the present value\n\n$[Fv]$, which refers to the future value\n\n$[type]$, which indicates the period basis of the computation\n \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":350,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/01fa8584ee65715bd9fb2e8063ac24fe/e9e58b5667b7eebab90c76589c66cc02/lateximg_large.png","width":780},"regular":{"height":176,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/01fa8584ee65715bd9fb2e8063ac24fe/e9e58b5667b7eebab90c76589c66cc02/lateximg.png","width":392}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"In calculating the loan payment using the PMT function, we will consider the following details from the problem.\n\n| Particulars   |          |\n|---------------|----------|\n| Interest rate | 6.8%     |\n| Period        | 5        |\n| Present value | $75,000  |\n\n\n\n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Since our computation focuses on the required repayment, the future value or FV in the PMT function should be zero, and the type is also zero, which indicates an end-of-year basis.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/01fa8584ee65715bd9fb2e8063ac24fe/cc3af35658ad47d0dd27b2cd1154bc1a/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/01fa8584ee65715bd9fb2e8063ac24fe/cc3af35658ad47d0dd27b2cd1154bc1a/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"Let's now calculate the annual loan payment using the spreadsheet.\n\n\n!['slader'](https://slader-solution-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/68f4a757-5e27-42bb-aeab-d01176c5d737-1640889333636962.png)\n\n**Based on our calculation, the annual loan payment to Prescott Bank should be $18,193.96.**","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"ee4e4e47-a465-4acd-b31b-41bbc10bf48b","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. 